    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Brazil (
                        Berle
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d575</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">575</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-23T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-23T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/8–2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-23T19:00:00-03:00">August 23, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 24—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2641. For Department and Freedman, FEA.<note n="16" xml:id="d575fn16">Walter
                        Freedman, Acting Director, Requirements and Supply Branch, Bureau of
                        Supplies, Foreign Economic Administration.</note> Department’s telegram
                    2047, August 22.<note n="17" xml:id="d575fn17">Not printed.</note> Foreign
                    Office informally but authoritatively states Brazil unconditionally accepts
                    liquidation of Decentralization Plan of export control. Formal note to this
                    effect is to be delivered by 25th. It is believed public announcement may safely
                    be made on basis of assurance received from office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
